{"groups": {"656": [], "2839": [], "1304": [["1304-001", "Term names the act of domineering over others as an exercise of power \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the disposition of the one who dominates (absence of the fear of God) and the moral contrast with restrained, God-fearing authority"]], "2806": [["2806-001", "Term names the act of domineering over others as an exercise of power \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the disposition of the one who dominates (absence of the fear of God) and the moral contrast with restrained, God-fearing authority"]], "2917": [["2917-001", "Term names the act of domineering over others as an exercise of power \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the disposition of the one who dominates (absence of the fear of God) and the moral contrast with restrained, God-fearing authority"]], "1314": [["1314-001", "Term names the capacity to rule or exercise power over others \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the divine granting of rule, the character of the one appointed to authority, and the demonstration that earthly power has limits before divine protection"]], "2813": [["2813-001", "Term names the capacity to rule or exercise power over others \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the divine granting of rule, the character of the one appointed to authority, and the demonstration that earthly power has limits before divine protection"]], "2918": [["2918-001", "Term names the capacity to rule or exercise power over others \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the divine granting of rule, the character of the one appointed to authority, and the demonstration that earthly power has limits before divine protection"]], "1313": [["1313-001", "Term names power as the capacity to command or control \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the recognition of the limits of human power over spirit and death, and through the prudent posture of subjects under sovereign authority"]], "2780": [["2780-001", "Term names power as the capacity to command or control \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the recognition of the limits of human power over spirit and death, and through the prudent posture of subjects under sovereign authority"]], "1312": [["1312-001", "Term names governing authority held by a person by God's appointment \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the exercise of that authority in providential circumstances that draw out submission, recognition, and the outworking of prior inner-being history"]], "2804": [["2804-001", "Term names governing authority held by a person by God's appointment \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the exercise of that authority in providential circumstances that draw out submission, recognition, and the outworking of prior inner-being history"]], "2872": [["2872-001", "Term names the multiplication of sin, transgression, iniquity, evil, and abomination \u2014 the inner being morally corrupted to an escalating degree"], ["2872-002", "Term names the multiplication of spiritual unfaithfulness \u2014 whoring after other gods, multiplying idolatrous altars, and escalating apostasy that provokes divine anger"], ["2872-003", "Term names the multiplication of inner-being suffering \u2014 pain, sorrow, mourning, vexation, distress, fear, and grief intensified to an overwhelming degree"], ["2872-004", "Term names the multiplication of wisdom, knowledge, understanding, and their counterparts \u2014 foolish excess of words, vanity of multiplied study, the breadth of mind God grants, and the limits of multiplied inquiry"], ["2872-005", "Term names the multiplication of divine grace \u2014 abundant pardon, plentiful redemption, enlargement of the inner being through divine gentleness, and divinely multiplied strength for the weary"], ["2872-006", "Term names multiplication as moral and covenantal consequence \u2014 increase predicated on obedience, prayer, inner posture, or wisdom reception; also divine multiplication of visions, signs, and words addressed to the inner being"]], "2877": [["2877-001", "Term names the growth of power and pride \u2014 addressed through prophetic vision as a warning to the inner being of the sovereign; the growing tree is the parabolic image of self-magnifying pride confronted by God"]], "2878": [["2878-001", "Term names greatness as divinely-granted sovereign power \u2014 the inner being engaged through the confrontation of pride, the experience of humiliation and restoration, the fear it produces in others, and the eschatological hope of its transfer to God's people"]], "1322": [["1322-001", "Term names the exercise of dominion \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the creational mandate to rule with responsibility, the character-revealing contrast between ruthless and righteous dominion, the experience of subjugation under oppressive rule, the messianic hope for just dominion, and the penetrating descent of divine judgment into the bones"]], "2897": [["2897-001", "Term names the exercise of dominion \u2014 the inner being is engaged through the creational mandate to rule with responsibility, the character-revealing contrast between ruthless and righteous dominion, the experience of subjugation under oppressive rule, the messianic hope for just dominion, and the penetrating descent of divine judgment into the bones"]], "2838": [], "2814": [], "2919": [], "2807": [["2807-001", "Term names the imperious, shameless inner disposition \u2014 a heart so sick with spiritual adultery that it acts with brazen boldness in its unfaithfulness"]], "2805": [["2805-001", "Term applied to God's sovereign rule over kingdoms \u2014 the inner being engaged through the repeated, humbling recognition that all human authority is derivative and that God gives power to whom he will; the great king's journey from pride to acknowledgement"]], "2916": [["2916-001", "Term applied to God's sovereign rule over kingdoms \u2014 the inner being engaged through the repeated, humbling recognition that all human authority is derivative and that God gives power to whom he will; the great king's journey from pride to acknowledgement"]], "2849": [["2849-001", "Term names divine might as the limit of human contention \u2014 the inner being confronted with the wisdom of submission before one stronger"]], "2847": [["2847-001", "Term names the prevailing of a superior force over a person \u2014 the inner being engaged through the wisdom of companionship against adversity, the recognition of divine prevailing power over mortal life, and the overwhelming of the soul by distress and anguish"]], "2850": [["2850-001", "Term names royal might as the object of pride \u2014 the inner being's self-glorification in its own power, at the very moment of divine judgment"]], "2851": [["2851-001", "Term names might as divinely bestowed \u2014 all royal power has its source in the God of heaven who gives and withholds; the inner being receives this as theological orientation"]], "2846": [["2846-001", "Term names the governor's exercise of authority at the boundary of the sacred \u2014 the inner being engaged through rulings on holy access, the conscience about sacred participation, and the pastoral-authoritative word that redirects communal grief toward holy joy"]], "1353": [["1353-001", "Term names the receiving of what is due \u2014 whether divine inheritance, adopted sonship, or inward penalty; the inner being engaged as recipient of consequence or promise"]], "1352": [["1352-001", "Term names the becoming of the inner being \u2014 transformation, formation, identity-shift, disclosure, and accountability; including becoming like Christ, becoming mature or childish, becoming a participant in good or evil, and the becoming-disclosed of the heart secrets"]], "1354": [["1354-001", "Term names the act of demonstrating \u2014 the inner being engaged as source or recipient of what is shown: love, earnestness, hope, conscience, divine power and wrath made visible through demonstration"]], "1331": [["1331-001", "Term names the inner-being goal of winning others \u2014 the motivating purpose behind Paul's self-subordination; love for others expressed as the drive to gain them for salvation"]], "1349": [["1349-001", "Term as the particle of inner-being warning \u2014 it marks the feared spiritual failure that vigilance must prevent: drifting, an unbelieving heart, falling short of rest"]], "1350": [["1350-001", "Term qualifies, grounds, and intensifies inner-being orientations \u2014 the particle marks how inner states are to be reckoned, how they arise from theological realities, and how they shape conduct; including self-examination, faith, conscience, apostasy, love, forgiveness, submission, ambition, and the reckoning of death to sin and life to God"]], "1334": [["1334-001", "Term names the filling or completing of the inner being \u2014 whether filled with joy, comfort, wisdom, knowledge, the Spirit, divine fullness, or moral corruption; and the fulfilment of calling, law, and obedience through love and Spirit-empowered character"]], "1348": [["1348-001", "Term names the sifting of the inner being by a hostile spiritual agent \u2014 the adversarial trial to which faith is subjected"]], "1340": [["1340-001", "Term names the coming or approach that engages the inner being through encounter with God \u2014 God coming to humans in theophany, warning, judgment and salvation; humans coming before God in prayer, worship, confession, and sacred entry; the day of the Lord approaching with dread or hope"], ["1340-002", "Term names the arrival of calamity, distress, dread, and mortality upon the inner being \u2014 the moment when feared things come, sighing replaces bread, evil comes instead of hoped-for good, and trouble arrives without rest"], ["1340-003", "Term in relational and covenantal entry with inner-being moral dimension \u2014 entering another person with longing, deception, desperation, or transgression; entering covenant commitment; and the purity implications of entering sacred or defiled space"]], "1333": [["1333-001", "Term names divine might as the object of praise and the source of human capacity \u2014 the inner being engaged through doxological recognition and grateful reception of divinely-given strength"]], "1346": []}, "assign": {"656": {"12705": [null, false], "12706": [null, false], "12709": [null, false]}, "2839": {"12705": [null, false], "12706": [null, false], "12709": [null, false]}, "1304": {"51263": ["1304-001", true]}, "2806": {"51263": ["2806-001", true]}, "2917": {"51263": ["2917-001", true]}, "1314": {"52540": ["1314-001", true], "52541": [null, false], "52542": ["1314-001", false], "52543": ["1314-001", false], "52544": [null, false], "52545": [null, false], "52546": [null, false]}, "2813": {"52540": ["2813-001", true], "52541": [null, false], "52542": ["2813-001", false], "52543": ["2813-001", false], "52544": [null, false], "52545": [null, false], "52546": [null, false]}, "2918": {"52540": ["2918-001", true], "52541": [null, false], "52542": ["2918-001", false], "52543": ["2918-001", false], "52544": [null, false], "52545": [null, false], "52546": [null, false]}, "1313": {"54664": ["1313-001", false], "54665": ["1313-001", true]}, "2780": {"54664": ["2780-001", false], "54665": ["2780-001", true]}, "1312": {"52257": ["1312-001", true]}, "2804": {"52257": ["2804-001", true]}, "2872": {"85504": [[null, false]], "85505": [[null, false]], "85506": [[null, false]], "85507": [[null, false]], "85508": [[null, false]], "85509": [[null, false]], "85511": [[null, false]], "85512": [[null, false]], "85513": [[null, false]], "85514": [[null, false]], "85515": [[null, false]], "85516": [[null, false]], "85517": [[null, false]], "85518": [[null, false]], "85519": [[null, false]], "85520": [[null, false]], "85521": [[null, false]], "85522": [[null, false]], "85524": [[null, false]], "85525": [[null, false]], "85529": [[null, false]], "85532": [[null, false]], "85534": [[null, false]], "85535"